---
title: Mediterranean Baked Veggies with Couscous, Almonds & Feta
description: We don’t mean to burst tomatoes’ bubble, but when you literally burst tomatoes in the oven, they become all the more delicious. And while we hate to imagine them straining, seizing, and shriveling under that sizzling heat, they come out on the other side with a flavor that’s concentrated and juicy. It allows them to hold their own against the assertive flavors in this dish, from briny feta cheese to grassy green asparagus.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/605a5aa0932040538e75dd59-07770f7e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mediterranean-baked-veggies-605a5aa0932040538e75dd59-447e47aa.pdf
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mediterranean-baked-veggies-605a5aa0932040538e75dd59
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Mediterranean
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 500 kcal
  fat: 19 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 68 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 15 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 720 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}; cut stalks crosswise into 3-inch-long pieces. Strip @thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

In a small #pot, combine @veggie stock concentrate{2} with @water{1%cup}. Bring to a simmer over medium heat.

> Use 2 cups water for 4 servings instead.

Toss garlic, asparagus, @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}, and half the chopped thyme on a #baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack, tossing halfway through, until asparagus is tender and tomatoes burst, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot over medium heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Israeli couscous{3/4%cup} and remaining chopped thyme to same pot. Cook, stirring, until grains are lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour stock into pot with couscous mixture. Reduce to a low simmer, then cover and cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Drain any excess liquid from pot if necessary.

Fluff couscous with a #fork; season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous between plates, then top with roasted veggies. Sprinkle with @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce}, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and scallion greens. Serve.